        <td class="text-lg"><strong>March - Sept. 2023</strong></td>
        <td class="text-lg">Master's student Chloé Dion</td>
      </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <br/>

  <div>
    <div class="mt-6 text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">Scientific presentation</div>
  </div>

  <div class="overflow-x-auto">
    <table class="table table-lg">
      <tbody>
      <tr>
              <td class="text-lg"><strong>March 2024</strong></td>
              <td class="text-lg">I gave a talk on my work at the Laboratoire d’Informatique de l’Université du Mans (LIUM) seminar on "Automatic Speech-to-Pictogram Translation to Facilitate Communication for People with Language Impairments".
              </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
              <td class="text-lg"><strong>June 2023</strong></td>
              <td class="text-lg">I presented my Ph.D. at the "Jeunes Chercheurs en Parole" group seminars. The talk is available on <a class="link-secondary link-hover" target="_blank" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SCVzv_Mc4wg">YouTube</a>.
              </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="text-lg"><strong>May 2022</strong></td>
        <td class="text-lg">I presented my Ph.D. subject at the Pint of Science Festival 2022: "From Speech to Pictograms". <br>Pint of Science is an international science festival aimed at bringing science outside the laboratory walls, in cafés or bars, engaging a non-expert audience.</td>
